ny </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">further </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">negative effe</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ct</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">on land available to let c</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ould have disastrous consequences for the sector.  Existing businesses would be unable to</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> expand without purchasing land, which would have consequen</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ces for their viability and ultimately</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> threaten food security.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Scottish Govern</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ment’s forthcoming review of agricultural holdings is ideally placed to review the issues with the current system</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">.  Meantime</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">, NFU Scotland believes that the Tenant Farming Forum is best placed to </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-si